HEADWORD: Creosol
<hw>Cre"o*sol</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧"⟦osl⟧*s⟦omac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Creos</ets>ote + phen<ets>ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A colorless liquid resembling phenol or carbolic acid, homologous
with pyrocatechin, and obtained from beechwood tar and gum
guaiacum.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>creasol</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Creosote</ent>⟦br⟧
